it with a rubber mallet a.";i:5;s:61:"I dont mind chair rails but in every room is a bit excessive.";i:6;s:72:"So we have slowly been removing them as I see fit when I repaint a room.";i:7;s:80:"I removed it from our family room and my daughters nursery and now my sons room.";i:8;s:74:"So now I consider myself a little bit of a pro on taking off a chair rail.";i:9;s:47:"Anyway Im getting a little bit ahead of things.";i:10;s:81:"So in my last post I showed you the actual process of taking down the chair rail.";i:11;s:135:"Before I show you the final reveal of the paint and such I wanted to give you the next steps to take once you have the chair rail down.";i:12;s:74:"Once you have the chair rail down you will be left with holes in the wall.";i:13;s:81:"Locate the studs in the wall and mark them with a pencil or bits of masking tape.";i:14;s:100:"Measure up from the floor andor use a level to mark the chair rail height at each end of each piece.";i:15;s:64:"Have an assistant help hold the chair rail at the marked height.";i:16;s:82:"To take apart the stair rail I started by hammering off the cap of the newel post.";i:17;s:74:"Beneath the blocking was a 44 post wrapped on all sides by 1x trim boards.";i:18;s:143:"Next I equipped my trusty reciprocating saw with a nail-cutting blade and sliced through the fasteners between the handrail and the newel post.";i:19;s:38:"This was the first time Ive removed a.";i:20;s:36:"REMOVE A STAIR LIFT CHAIR AND TRACK.";i:21;s:121:"CAN ANYONE TELL ME HOW TO REMOVE A STAIR LIFT CHAIR FROM THE TRACK ON WHICH IT RIDES and the the track from the stairway.";i:22;s:148:"My son brought a house and it were left in placeCAN THE TRACK BE REMOVE IN TWO PARTS IT 13 LONGTHIS IS A STANNAH MODEL 420 STRAIGHT TRACK THANK YOU.";i:23;s:165:"When you remove the chair rail make sure to hammer the nails out or hammer them flat so that no one can get hurt on all those sharp nails sticking out of the boards.";i:24;s:56:"When you are done you will have the nail holes to patch.";i:25;s:71:"You will also most likely have other things that need patching as well.";i:26;s:43:"Use a putty knife to remove the chair rail.";i:27;s:20:"Watch out for nails.";i:28;s:30:"Sandscrape any rough surfaces.";i:29;s:88:"Use drywall patching compound to fill in nail holes and rough edges level with the wall.";i:30;s:22:"Let it dry over night.";i:31;s:59:"Next day use a damp sponge over the patch to smooth it out.";i:32;s:174:"We recently removed a chair rail in a house that we purchased and started to patch holes and wall imperfections before I got worried that we werent qualified to fix the wall.";i:33;s:127:"Ive reached out to some local painters and they are saying that this is a orange peel textured wall when they look at pictures.";i:34;s:102:"On most units the chair needs to be removed from the top of the rail and then carried down the stairs.";i:35;s:67:"The chair itself is bulky and has significant weight so be careful.";i:36;s:78:"The track is made of aluminum and will definitely need two people to carry it.";i:37;s:77:"There are several options for removal once a stairlift is no longer required.";i:38;s:87:"Slide the wide putty knife flat against the wall starting at one end of the chair rail.";i:39;s:46:"Press the knife between the trim and the wall.";i:40;s:94:"You may need to work along the wall at first before you find a place where the knife will fit.";i:41;s:55:"Tip the knife toward you gently enough to open the gap.";i:42;s:146:"Chair rail that isnt chair rail I like wide chair rail in certain circumstances such as when youre in a room that has 9 or taller ceiling heights.";i:43;s:109:"This was a small waiting room 10 x 12 and I just thought it overpowered the room with its dimensional height.";i:44;s:20:"I guess it looks ok.";i:45;s:108:"A chair rail is a piece of molding made of wood plastic or composite placed on a wall at the top of a chair.";i:46;s:44:"It is designed to protect walls from damage.";i:47;s:120:"Updating